{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, there's been a push towards defining and implementing computational-based triage code assignment mechanisms to minimize human-related errors 19, 20.",
    "Many authors have explored the potential of automated systems based on computational intelligence to improve triage by suggesting emergency codes 19, 20.",
    "Furthermore, machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) algorithms have demonstrated the ability to analyze electronic medical records (EMRs) and unstructured patient data from sensors or wearable devices 21, 22.",
    "As triage systems rely on patient data observation, ML and AI have been investigated to enhance classical clinical scoring systems 9.",
    "Numerous prediction models have been developed to refine the triage process, offering more nuanced patient stratification within traditional groups and improving clinical outcomes 8, 9."
  ]
}